# __TEAM_NAME__ Workspace

Claude Code workspace for the __TEAM_NAME__ team.

## Quickstart

```bash
gh repo clone your-org/__TEAM_SLUG__-workspace
cd __TEAM_SLUG__-workspace
make setup            # clone all repos
make setup-full       # clone + bootstrap deps
```

## Migrating from existing repos

If you already have some of these repos cloned elsewhere, move them into the workspace directory before running setup:

```bash
mv ~/code/my-repo __TEAM_SLUG__-workspace/my-repo
```

Then run `make setup` — the setup script automatically skips repos that already exist in the workspace directory.

## Commands

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `make setup` | Clone all repos |
| `make setup-full` | Clone + bootstrap deps |
| `make update` | Pull latest across all cloned repos |
| `make status` | Git status for all repos |
| `make search QUERY='...'` | Search across all repos |
| `make gitignore` | Regenerate .gitignore from repos.json |
| `make help` | Show all targets |

## Adding a repo

1. Add it to `repos.json`
2. Run `make gitignore` to update .gitignore
3. Run `make setup` (only clones the new repo, skips existing ones)
4. Update `.claude/CLAUDE.md` with the repo's purpose and relationships
5. Commit and push

## Prerequisites

**Required:**
- `gh` (GitHub CLI) — must be authenticated (`gh auth status` to check)
- `git`
- `jq`

**Recommended:**
- `docker` — required for some local dev workflows

## Recommended Claude Code plugins

The setup script will prompt you to install these. You can also install manually:

| Plugin | What it does |
|--------|-------------|
| `code-simplifier` | Reviews changed code for clarity and efficiency |
| `skill-creator` | Create, modify, and eval custom skills |
| `context7` | Fetches up-to-date library docs during sessions |

```bash
claude plugin install code-simplifier@claude-plugins-official
claude plugin install skill-creator@claude-plugins-official
claude plugin install context7@claude-plugins-official
```

## What is Claude Code?

[Claude Code](https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code) is Anthropic's CLI tool that gives Claude direct access to your codebase. This workspace includes a shared `CLAUDE.md` that teaches Claude about your repos, how they connect, deployment patterns, and team conventions — so every engineer on the team gets the same high-quality AI assistance out of the box.

## Personal overrides

Create `CLAUDE.local.md` (gitignored) for personal preferences, or `.claude/settings.local.json` for personal permission overrides. Neither is shared with the team.

